<item>
            <title>[SPR-13612] Skip Content-Disposition header when requestUri is the context and/or the servlet path</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13612</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The fix to protect against RFD exploits (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-13548&quot; title=&quot;Protect against RFD exploits&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-13548&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-13548&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) introduced a &quot;Content-Disposition:attachment;filename=f.txt&quot; response header for @ResponseBody methods where the URL appears to have an extension that is neither whitelisted by default nor explicitly registered by the application.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However if you name an application with Maven conventions my-app.1.3.4-SNAPSHOT and deploy to a servlet container a Content-Disposition header is added for the URLs that match the context and/or servlet path.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="66467">SPR-13612</key>
            <summary>Skip Content-Disposition header when requestUri is the context and/or the servlet path</summary>
